  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare the benefit of cardiac resynchronization therapy
      (CRT)-therapy in patients with a QRS-complex of 120-150 ms to patients with a QRS-complex of
      &gt; 150 ms.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this study is to compare the benefit of CRT-therapy in patients with a
      QRS-complex of 120-150 ms to patients with a QRS-complex of &gt; 150 ms within 12 months. A
      benefit is defined as change in quality of life and change in physical ability.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
